Business Brief -- Limited Inc.:
   Retailer Reports Net Rose
   16% for Its Fourth Quarter
For the period ended Feb. 1, net income climbed to $200.3
million, or 55 cents a share, from $172.2 million, or 48
cents a share, in the year-ago period. Sales were $2.06
billion, up 18% from $1.74 billion.
   For the fiscal year, the Columbus, Ohio, apparel retailer
earned $403.3 million, or $1.11 a share, compared with $398.4
million, or $1.10 a share, in the prior year ended Feb. 2.
Sales were up 17% to $6.15 billion from $5.25 billion.
   On the plus side, Mr. Wexner said that the Express women's
division topped $1 billion in sales for the first time. He
also singled out the men's Structure division, noting that it
more than doubled its sales in 1991.